    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The FEA modeling framework demonstrates adequate credibility for the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending COU based on the assessed factors. All quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs) are satisfied. The below-threshold Test Conditions factor is acknowledged and accepted given the scope limitation to ASTM F1717 static protocol. Two factors — Relevance of QoIs and Relevance of validation activities to COU — were not assessed, as the team judged their formal evaluation to be beyond the scope of the current submission phase. The overall credibility is considered sufficient for a Medium assurance level determination at this stage.",
